  "body": "With the current Optimism code, using Docker 20.10.8 and docker-compose 1.25.5:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# docker-compose build && echo \"Build complete\"\r\nERROR: The Compose file './docker-compose.yml' is invalid because:\r\nservices.batch_submitter.build contains unsupported option: 'target'\r\nservices.dtl.build contains unsupported option: 'target'\r\nservices.deployer.build contains unsupported option: 'target'\r\nservices.integration_tests.build contains unsupported option: 'target'\r\nservices.relayer.build contains unsupported option: 'target'\r\n```\r\n\r\nSee this similar issue someone filed against Docker in 2018: https://github.com/docker/compose/issues/5714\r\n\r\n> The issue was I've used version 3 which is not the latest from 3.x series as I thought. One needs to use at least version 3.4 for build target to work.\r\n\r\nAfter modifying docker-compose.yml to change the \"3\" to \"3.7\", per the above issue:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# docker-compose build && echo \"Build complete\"\r\nWARNING: Some services (gas_oracle, integration_tests, replica, verifier) use the 'deploy' key, which will be ignored. Compose does not support 'deploy' configuration - use `docker stack deploy` to deploy to a swarm.\r\nWARNING: Native build is an experimental feature and could change at any time\r\nBuilding l1_chain\r\n[+] Building 21.5s (11/11) FINISHED\r\n...\r\n```",
